[532.34923, "o", "\u001b[m"]
[532.349453, "o", "\r\n       \u001b[1m-n\u001b[0m, \u001b[1m--lines\u001b[0m \u001b[4mnumber\u001b[24m\u001b[m\r\n           Specify the \u001b[4mnumber\u001b[24m of lines per screenful. The \u001b[4mnumber\u001b[24m argument is a\u001b[m\r\n           positive decimal integer. The \u001b[1m--lines\u001b[0m option shall override any\u001b[m\r\n           values obtained from any other source, such as number of lines\u001b[m\r\n           reported by terminal.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m-\u001b[0m\u001b[4mnumber\u001b[24m\u001b[m\r\n           A numeric option means the same as \u001b[1m--lines\u001b[0m option argument.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m+\u001b[0m\u001b[4mnumber\u001b[24m\u001b[m\r\n           Start displaying each file at line \u001b[4mnumber\u001b[24m.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m+\u001b[0m/\u001b[4mstring\u001b[24m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page more(1) line 49 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[532.693304, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[532.693513, "o", "           The \u001b[4mstring\u001b[24m to be searched in each file before starting to display it.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m-h\u001b[0m, \u001b[1m--help\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n           Display help text and exit.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1m-V\u001b[0m, \u001b[1m--version\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n           Print version and exit.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[1mCOMMANDS\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n       Interactive commands for \u001b[1mmore\u001b[0m are based on \u001b[1mvi\u001b[0m(1). Some commands may be\u001b[m\r\n       preceded by a decimal number, called k in the descriptions below. In the\u001b[m\r\n       following descriptions, \u001b[1m^X\u001b[0m means \u001b[1mcontrol-X\u001b[0m.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mh\u001b[0m or \u001b[1m?\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page more(1) line 63 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[532.955065, "o", "\r\u001b[K"]
[532.955122, "o", "           Help; display a summary of these commands. If you forget all other\u001b[m\r\n           commands, remember this one.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mSPACE\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n           Display next k lines of text. Defaults to current screen size.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mz\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n           Display next k lines of text. Defaults to current screen size.\u001b[m\r\n           Argument becomes new default.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n       \u001b[1mRETURN\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n           Display next k lines of text. Defaults to 1. Argument becomes new\u001b[m\r\n           default.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page more(1) line 77 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
